content.text:
A recursive function is like a regular function but calls itself. It follows this syntax:
return_type function_name(parameters) {
  // Base case
  if(condition) return value;
  // Recursive call
  return function_name(modified_parameters);
}
The base case is critical to prevent infinite recursion.

